eshmun.gui.kripke

Interface GraphPanelContainer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    KripkeGraphPanelContainer, MultiKripkeGraphPanelContainer

    public interface GraphPanelContainer
    This class represents a GraphPanelContainer, it could be anything as long as it provides a method that returns the current GraphPanel instance in use.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kinan Dak Al Bab

      • getSaveObjects

        SaveObject[] getSaveObjects()
        Constructs an array of saveObject that could be used to save the structure in this Container.

        If this container contained a single KripkeStructure,then this would be an array of a single element, if this contained MultipKripkeStrcture then the array would contain the saveObjects related to the nested Kripke Structure.

        Returns:
        array of saveObject to save the structure in this GraphPanel.

      • constructCurrentStructure

        Repairable constructCurrentStructure()
        Constructs a Repair-able Structure that reflects the data Currently Visible inside Eshmun. This is equivalent to constructStructure when used with a KripkeGraphPanelContainer, but if it was used with a composite container, it will return the structure currently in focus inside the composite container.
        Returns:
        a repair-able structure representing what is inside the container.
